Plus, Cassius talks about key factors to consider when buying your first (or second or third) gimbal!

Learn more about FiLMiC Pro via the link in our bio! ​​​

node.text:
#Cinematch — the camera matching plugin from the makers of @FilmConvert — has just received support for #FiLMiCPro Log V3* which is available on 12 series 10-bit capable iPhones. Now you can quickly match your #iPhone12 footage shot in FiLMiC Log V3 to cameras from #Blackmagic, #ARRI, #RED, #Sony, and #Fujifilm - in just a few clicks! 

In this #tutorial, you will learn not only what is possible when using Cinematch (#DavinciResolve or #PremierePro) and FiLMiC Log V3, but also how to use Cinematch in Davinci Resolve.

* Log V3 is part of the cinematographer kit and available as an optional in-app purchase in FiLMiC Pro and available on 10-bit capable 12 series iPhones only.

#cinematography #videography #mobilevideo #filmmaking #mobilefilmmaking #FiLMiC #FilmConvert #colorgrade #colorgrading #smartphonefilmmaking

node.title: Using FilmConvert's Cinematch Plug-in with FiLMiC Pro Log V3

"In late 2018, filmmaker Sven Dreesbach headed to the #IndianOcean to document the #Maldives Whale Shark Research Programme, a marine-wildlife research charity. He came back with an eight-minute film, shot entirely on an #iPhone XS with #FiLMiCPro, that tells the conservationists’ story in gorgeous detail."

Go #BehindTheShot and learn how filmmaker Sven Dreesbach created his gorgeous #underwater short #documentary on the #whalesharks of the Maldives with FiLMiC Pro in this #AppStore feature story! Read the whole article via the link in our bio!

@9to5mac invites you to "share your best L.A. photos shot on #iPhone of the places and people close to your heart" to celebrate the opening of the new #Apple Tower Theatre store. 

Share your best photos on Twitter or Instagram (we humbly suggest shooting them with our #Firstlight photo app), tag @michaelsteeber, and 9to5Mac will highlight some of their favorites.

p.s. In celebration of L.A.’s film history, they’ll also gift one photographer a free copy of #FiLMiCPro to kickstart (or amplify) a passion for #mobilefilmmaking!
